Cell[TextData[{
 "\n\n\n",
 StyleBox["Populating the Grid\n", "Subsection"],
 "In \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]site percolation,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] each \
site on the lattice is either occupied (conductive/open) or empty \
(blocked/closed) based on a probability ",
 StyleBox["p",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". ",
 StyleBox["RandomChoice", "Code"],
 " populates the ",
 StyleBox["n \[Times] n",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " grid, assigning values based on weights {",
 StyleBox["p",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", 1-",
 StyleBox["p",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "}.\n\n\[FilledSmallCircle] ",
 StyleBox["Probability p",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ": Determines the density of occupied sites.\n\[FilledSmallCircle] ",
 StyleBox["Manipulate Interface",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ": A slider controls ",
 StyleBox["p",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " (ranging from 0 to 1) alongside a \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Refresh\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] button.\n\[FilledSmallCircle] ",
 StyleBox["Visualization",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ": ",
 StyleBox["ArrayPlot", "Code"],
 " displays the resulting random configuration. This static noise \
visualization verifies site distribution behavior before clustering \
algorithms are applied."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.969591768660391*^9, 3.969591780714512*^9}, 
   3.9698565126195965`*^9, {3.9769611795952168`*^9, 3.9769612054477863`*^9}, 
